title: Grateful Dead Live at Long Beach Arena on 1985-11-16
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 11/2015
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket-> Sugaree-> El Paso, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Little Red Rooster, West L.A. Fadeaway, Let It Grow

Set 2

Tennessee Jed, Cumberland Blues, I Need A Miracle-> Crazy Fingers-> Drums-> Comes A Time-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> Truckin'-> Black Peter-> Good Lovin', E: Day Job

reviews.review_text: Nak 300 CP4 John was known to run Nak 304's generally from the back half of the venue with them flying 20 feet in the air. There was a time during the 80 's where John had the longest run of Dead shows.
Good recording. Good Show Super fine Comes a Time goes HOT into Gimme Some Lovin' featuring extra Phil.
